author: JJ Nattrass
title: EastEnders is cancelled TONIGHT to make way for FA Cup - and fans are fuming
text:
EastEnders has been cancelled tonight Share Get soaps   Thank you for subscribing!   
It has a loyal fan base, which in turn has earned it some of the biggest accolades in TV. 
But EastEnders ' viewers are set to be disappointed tonight as the show's regular slot BBC One at 8pm has been nabbed by the football. 
The BBC has confirmed that it has rescheduled the programme to make way for Arsenal's fifth-round match against Sutton United, leaving viewers disappointed for the third time in two months. Read More Lee Ryan's joining EastEnders as Walford's new blue eyed boy - and he's set to cause a stir The BBC confirmed the FA cup would be shown instead on Monday 
Monday evening's episode has been bumped off the channel thanks to the match kicking-off at 7.55pm, with a build-up starting at 7.30pm. 
But while there are undoubtedly many football fans delighted at the opportunity to catch the show, fans of Albert Square have taken to Twitter to vent their anger. 
A disappointed @Jadeyyogom wrote: "How many more times does #eastenders have to be replaced by football!!! Oh wait its happening again on Monday." Something that left many fans raging (Photo: bbceastenders/Twitter) 
And sharing her sentiments, @leeannemccourtx tweeted: "@BBCOne. @bbceastenders. so why not cancel another programme for football fed up you always take of eastenders #not happy." 
This isn't the first time the show has been cancelled in favour of football, as January's epic bus crash cliffhanger was also postponed for another match - with viewers left outraged they had to wait. 
Earlier that month they were once-again left raging and perplexed when an episode was pulled that tied in the tragic after-math of Ronnie and Roxy Mitchell. Read More This isn't the first time it's been cancelled this year (Photo: BBC) Though there was good news in the form of Lee Ryan joining the cast (Photo: BBC) 
Fans are currently immersed in the tragic and fraught demise of Lee and Whitney Carter's fledgling marriage, after the Lee (Danny-Boy Hatchard) left his wife (Shona McGarty) on Valentines day. 
But, as usual, show bosses have made sure its not all doom and gloom, as they announced on Thursday that there would be some fresh eye-candy heading to Albert Square . 
The 33-year-old Blue singer is set to play Walford's new bad boy, 'Woody' Woodward, a character who has led a "colourful life" to date. Read More
